node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'For most, playing it cool means to be unemotional, indifferent, detached, withheld, and as if you don't care about anything. This is the antithesis of intimacy and connection.'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'Whatever you do, don't play it cool, don't play games, don't be unemotional, and definitely don't hold back. Be your whole entire self. This is what it means to connect and be vulnerable.'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'If a relationship is what you seek this is the worst possible advice to follow. Not only will you attract unavailable partners but you yourself are unavailable and potentially unsafe.'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'Expecting someone to chase while you expressing indifference is a recipe for disconnection. This is also a major reenactment of unresolved wounds. This is the pattern that many people likely need to break. @scncarestie'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'Withholding parts of ourselves is connected to shame and insecurity. When we withhold or avoid we send ourselves the implicit message, "This part of me is reject-able, I better wait."'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'By contrast, when we take a risk and share a vulnerable part of ourselves we gain the opportunity to be seen and accepted. This is the reparative resolution that we seek in our adult relationships.'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'If you're seeking connection, act like you care. Like a lot. And not through subtle cues or hints. Make sure to explicitly express you interest. Ask all the Share parts questions. yourself.'.

Photo shared by self love | mental health ♥ on August 27, 2021 tagging @selfcare4yu, and @selfloveblossom. May be an image of text that says 'Sure, if you want to wait until you feel comfy take your time But do make sure to put your entire self out there. Vulnerability creates intimacy, intimacy creates connection, and a connection creates a relationship.'.
